Titolo: Floyd of the Jungle

Anno: 1982

Descrizione: Floyd of the Jungle is a 1982 platform game for the Atari 8-bit family and part of the initial batch of games from  MicroProse. Designed and programmed by company co-founder Sid Meier, it is one of the few 2D action games he created and the only platform game. It allows up to four players at once.
The 1982 release is written in Atari BASIC. A second version, published in 1983, is programmed in assembly language for improved performance, and the computer controls any unused players. Version 2 was available for both the Atari 8-bit family and Commodore 64.

Genere: Platform 

Valutazione: N/A
